node.text: With the passing of US Senator & Presidential candidate Mike Gravel, the US & world have lost a great voice for peace & responsible foreign policy. I had the privilege of speaking to him many times throughout my campaign, and every time, his sincere and enduring commitment to this cause shined through. My deeper condolences go out to the Gravel family & his loved ones.

node.text:
President Biden, we need you to be the president who has the vision and courage to move us into a 21st century of peace and prosperity; ratchet down the new cold war with Russia and China, replacing the policy of confrontation with cooperation, so we can work together addressing issues affecting all of humanity, such as nuclear proliferation, climate change, pandemics, terrorism, and human trafficking.

Mr. President, we need you to be the leader who will stand up against the warmongers who dream of a never-ending, always-escalating cold war to fill their bank accounts and fuel their political ambitions, with complete disregard for the fact that such a new cold war will eventually and inevitably end in a nuclear holocaust. President Biden, we need you to end this new cold war before it's too late.

The mob who stormed the Capitol to try to stop Congress from carrying out its constitutional responsibilities were behaving like domestic enemies of our country. But let’s be clear, the John Brennan's, Adam Schiffs and the oligarchs in Big Tech who are trying to undermine our constitutionally-protected rights and turn our country into a police state with KGB-style "surveillance" are also domestic enemies—and much more powerful, and therefore dangerous, than the mob which stormed the Capitol. 

John Brennan said, “Members of the Biden team who have been nominated or have been appointed are now moving in laser like fashion to try to uncover as much as they can about what looks very similar to insurgency movements that we've seen overseas, where they germinate in different parts of the country and they gain strength and it brings together an unholy alliance frequently of religious extremists, authoritarians, fascists, bigots, racists, Nativists, even libertarians.”
 
President Biden, I call upon you and all members of Congress from both parties to denounce these efforts by the likes of Brennan and others to take away our civil liberties endowed to us by our Creator and guaranteed in our Constitution. If you don’t stand up to these people now, then our country will be in great peril.

node.text: With the passing of US Senator & Presidential candidate Mike Gravel, the US & world have lost a great voice for peace & responsible foreign policy. I had the privilege of speaking to him many times throughout my campaign, and every time, his sincere and enduring commitment to this cause shined through. My deeper condolences go out to the Gravel family & his loved ones.

node.text: I’m so grateful for the gift of yoga. It has impacted my life in the most profound way. I’ve been practicing yoga asanas and yoga meditation for as long as I can remember, and it remains central to my daily practice. It is so much more than a form of physical exercise. It is a lifestyle, a consciousness and worldview that can inspire us to respect and care for one another and our planet. #internationalyogaday

node.text: Just a girl and her dad, singing a song of praise and worship and God’s love. Dad, today is the day we get to celebrate you and thank you for being the most amazing father any of us could ever wish for. I’m so grateful to be your daughter, and to walk down the path of this life with you by my side - as my dad and my friend. Your selflessness and focus on loving and serving God with your life, following Jesus Christ’s first and second commandments, continues to be such an inspiration to me. I love you! Happy Father’s Day, dad. I can’t wait to see you again. 🙏🏽

node.text: This Memorial Day, I remember and honor my brothers and sisters in uniform who made the ultimate sacrifice. Their courage and selflessness will never be forgotten. We honor them by taking care of our troops who serve today & making sure that the missions they are sent on are worthy of their great sacrifice.

node.text: To my mom: I’m so grateful for your unconditional love, tireless support, and indomitable spirit. I love you!!! (This picture was from January 2006 when I came home from Iraq.) Happy Mother’s Day to all the moms and mom-figures in your lives!!
I was inspired and moved by Tyler Perry’s sincere, powerful message of compassion and love which we so badly need right now. Only love can defeat hate. Please share widely.
